{"description":"Abstract ecosystem was where I met Ely. He joined with a bang, found his jam and started Max Abstracting everyone! 

Jokes apart, Ely is not only an awesome creator but also a passionate crypto warrior. 

qualities based on my experiences with him

1. Top tier creator with market pulse - Versatile content with current focus on live streaming & videos. From interviews to walkthroughs, everything executed with top entertainment value. Understands and acts on meta.

3. Bold - Doesn't shy away to experiement with new projects. Sometimes it can be harmful to him and his community if projects rug however he is upfront about risks involved. 

4. Top Abstract mindshare - Almost always within the top 10 on any time frame for Abstract ecosystem.

translation.translatedDescription:
As someone who studied cybersecurity, I really appreciate Beau‚Äôs work. He‚Äôs one of the few actually preaching security best practices in this space.

The harsh truth? Most people only care about security after something goes wrong‚Äîafter the hack, the exploit, the lost funds. If more people followed accounts like Beau‚Äôs before disaster strikes, we‚Äôd avoid so many preventable catastrophes.

So yeah, huge respect for what you‚Äôre doing. You‚Äôre out here saving people from themselves, and that‚Äôs no small feat. Keep being that white knight in a space that desperately needs more of them.

translation.translatedDescription:
Let's be real - you hardly ever see women in web3 who are actually about it. When you do, it's usually just... well, you know how it goes. (I know that sounds harsh, but let's keep it 100 - most women in this space are just... there.) But Marianne? She's different. She's rooted in a way you rarely see.

Her tenacity is next-level. Seriously, what a woman. She's been riding for Abstract since day one, never wavering in her enthusiasm for this ecosystem. And we're talking real support - back when she was going all in, morning to night, nothing but Abstract on her mind.

When 99% of people would've started slowing down, then eventually tapped out (and that's just human nature - no shade to Abstract), she kept that same energy. Unshakable endurance. For that alone, she deserves the title of Abstract's #1 supporter. The way she's everywhere at once?
